<TITLE> Adidas to invest 100 mln pounds in 2012 Olympics </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - German sports goods maker Adidas said on Thursday it will invest 100 million pounds ($200.1 million) in the 2012 Olympic games in London. Adidas Chief Executive Herbert Hainer, in London for a news conference with the organising committee of the games, said this was the biggest single investment Adidas has ever put into a UK sporting event. "We want to become the leading sportswear brand in the UK, Europe's largest sportswear market," Hainer said
